Reinforcement learning is not used to train the state-of-the-art text summarization model. The Machine Learning algorithm for training text summarization model requires labelled data.
question_results.question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Unsupervised learning is used to train the state-of-the-art text summarization model.
question_results.combined_program:
set(auto).
assign(max_seconds, 5).
assign(max_mem, 1024).
# Predicates:
CategorizedAs(x, y) ::: Machine Learning algorithm x is categorized as y.
SupervisedLearning(x) ::: x is supervised learning.
UnsupervisedLearning(x) ::: x is unsupervised learning.
ReinforcementLearning(x) ::: x is reinforcement learning.
Requires(x, y) ::: x requires y.
LabeledData(x) ::: x is labelled data.
StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(x) ::: x is the state-of-the-art text summarization model.
TrainedWith(x, y) ::: x is trained with y.
MachineLearningAlgorithm(x) ::: x is a Machine Learning algorithm.
UsedToTrain(x, y) ::: x is used to train y.
TextSummarizationModel(x) ::: x is a text summarization model.

# Premises:
∀x (MachineLearningAlgorithm(x) → (SupervisedLearning(x) ∨ UnsupervisedLearning(x) ∨ ReinforcementLearning(x)))
∀x (UnsupervisedLearning(x) → ¬Requires(x, LabeledData))
∀x (TrainedWith(StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel, x) → MachineLearningAlgorithm(x))
∀x (ReinforcementLearning(x) → ¬UsedToTrain(x, StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel))
∀x (MachineLearningAlgorithm(x) ∧ Requires(x, LabeledData) → TrainedWith(StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel, x))
∀x (MachineLearningAlgorithm(x) ∧ TrainedWith(StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel, x) → Requires(x, LabeledData))

# Conclusion:
∀x ((MachineLearningAlgorithm(x) ∧ Requires(x, LabeledData) ∧ TrainedWith(StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel, x)) → UnsupervisedLearning(x))
